        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Account recovery keys in Firefox Accounts]]></title>
            <link>https://mozilla.github.io/application-services/blog/2018/09/10/account-recovery-in-firefox-accounts.html</link>
            <guid>https://mozilla.github.io/application-services/blog/2018/09/10/account-recovery-in-firefox-accounts.html</guid>
            <pubDate>Mon, 10 Sep 2018 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2><a class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" id="account-recovery-keys-in-firefox-account"></a><a href="#account-recovery-keys-in-firefox-account" aria-hidden="true" class="hash-link"><svg class="hash-link-icon" aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Account recovery keys in Firefox Account</h2>
<p>The Firefox Accounts (FxA) team is in the process of releasing a
new feature called Account Recovery. This feature is aimed at
solving one of the most frustrating issues for our users. When
a user resets their account password, they risk losing data such
as synced bookmarks, passwords and browsing history. FxA encrypts
synced browser data with the userâ€™s account password in order to
protect their privacy. Resetting the password destroys the
encryption key and leaves the data inaccessible which
eventually is deleted.</p>
]]></description>
        </item>
